'''Biochemical detection''' is the [[science]] and [[technology]] of detecting [[Biochemistry|biochemical]]s and their [[concentration]] where trace analysis is concerned this is usually done by using a [[quartz crystal microbalance]], which measures a [[Linear density|mass per unit area]] by measuring the change in [[frequency]] of a [[quartz crystal]] [[resonator]].  Another method is with [[nanoparticle]]s.<ref>{{Cite news |date={{Date|2010-03-23}} |journal=[[Nature (journal)|Nature]] |doi=10.1038/news.2010.143 |title=Nanoparticle kit could diagnose disease early |first=Katharine |last=Sanderson }}</ref>

